<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id7a278d59-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="miscellaneous" id="id7a278d5a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Wage Rate Requirements</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">For provisions relating to rates of wages to be paid to laborers and mechanics on projects for construction, alteration, or repair work funded under div. D or an amendment by div. D of <ref href="/us/pl/117/58">Pub. L. 117–58</ref>, including authority of Secretary of Labor, see <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s18851">section 18851 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare.</p>
</note>
